    "methodology": "Self-reported work-related ill health data comes from the Labour Force Survey (LFS), a household survey of approximately 80,000 individuals per quarter. Cases are self-reported, which means they depend on respondents attributing illness to work. Days lost figures are also LFS-based. Fatal injury data comes from RIDDOR mandatory employer reports and is considered highly reliable. Cost estimates are modelled by HSE economists using a combination of direct costs (healthcare, lost output) and human costs (quality-adjusted life years lost). Sector rates are age-standardised to account for differing workforce demographics.",
